## 1. Overview

The **Automated Reprocess Manager (ARM)** is a desktop application used by operations teams to identify and reprocess **failed Finished Goods (FG) serial numbers** that did not complete their synchronization workflow. ARM connects to a central SQL database, retrieves failure records, and replays each message through the configured web service endpoint — all without leaving the application.

Key capabilities:

- Filter failures by **Pool**, **Synchronization Queue**, and **date/time range** (CET timezone)
- View failed FG serial numbers with their failure timestamp and reason
- Reprocess one, several, or all failed items in a single click
- Automatically advance to the next Sync Queue when all items in the current queue have been reprocessed
- View detailed per-item results (order number, API response status)
- Export results to Excel for reporting

