## 3. Configuration

ARM reads all sensitive settings from a `.env` file located in the same directory as the application executable (or the project root when running from source).

### Required `.env` Keys

```env
# Web service endpoint for reprocessing
WEB_SERVICES=https://your-service-endpoint/api/run

# Database connection
DB2_DRIVER=ODBC Driver 17 for SQL Server
DB2_SERVER=your-server-name
DB2_DATABASE=your-database-name
DB2_TRUSTED=yes
```

> **Important:** The application will refuse to start if `WEB_SERVICES` is not set. Ensure the `.env` file is present before launching.

### SQL Files

ARM expects the following SQL query files inside a `sql/` subdirectory relative to the application:

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `sql/PROD_SQ.sql` | Fetches the list of Synchronization Queues for a given pool and date range |
| `sql/FailedFG.sql` | Retrieves failed FG serial numbers matching the selected filters |
| `sql/AIOT03_BasedOnFG.sql` | Retrieves the raw messages to replay for a given FG serial number |
| `sql/FetchOrderBaseOnFG.sql` | Looks up the Order Number associated with an FG serial number |

