## 9. Processing Log Reference

The log panel timestamps every entry. Common messages and their meanings:

| Log Message | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `Search started…` | Background search thread has begun |
| `Loaded N record(s).` | Search completed successfully |
| `No failed FG Serial Numbers found.` | No failures match the current filters |
| `Processing: <serial>` | ARM is querying the DB and calling the API for this serial |
| `<serial> → Success` | API returned HTTP 200 or 201 |
| `<serial> → Failed (HTTP NNN)` | API returned an unexpected status code |
| `<serial> → Request error: ...` | Network issue, timeout, or connection refused |
| `<serial> done — Success: N, Failed: N` | Summary for a serial with multiple messages |
| `<serial> already processed — skipping` | Serial was already reprocessed in this session |
| `Reprocess All completed.` | All items finished |
| `Auto-advancing: A → B` | Moving to next sync queue automatically |
| `✓ All sync queues for this pool have been processed.` | No more queues to advance to |

