## 10. Error Handling

| Situation | What happens |
|---|---|
| `.env` missing or `WEB_SERVICES` not set | Application refuses to start with an error message |
| Database connection failure | An error dialog is shown; the log records the exception detail |
| SQL file not found | The operation fails with a log entry; other operations are unaffected |
| API call times out (> 30 seconds) | Logged as `Request error: ...`; processing continues with the next serial |
| API returns non-200 status | Logged as `Failed (HTTP NNN)`; the response body is stored for export |
| No records found after Search | `No failed FG Serial Numbers found.` is logged; no error dialog |
| Reprocess clicked with empty table | Warning dialog: `No records to reprocess.` |
| Reprocess Selected with nothing selected | Warning dialog: `Select at least one Serial Number.` |

All background errors are caught and logged without crashing the application. The UI remains responsive in all cases.

