## 12. Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: The Sync Queue dropdown is empty or shows "No Data Found" after I select a pool. What should I check?**

Verify that the selected Pool has records in the Sync Queue table for the chosen date range. Try widening the date range. Also confirm the `sql/PROD_SQ.sql` file is present and the database is reachable.

---

**Q: I clicked Reprocess All but some items show "already processed — skipping". Why?**

ARM tracks which serial numbers have been processed within the current session to prevent duplicate submissions. If you ran Reprocess Selected or Reprocess All earlier in the same session, those serials are remembered. Clicking Search again clears the tracker and allows reprocessing.

---

**Q: The auto-advance did not trigger after Reprocess All. Why?**

Auto-advance only fires after **Reprocess All**, not after Reprocess Selected. It also requires the current Sync Queue value to exist in the refreshed queue list for the pool. If the queue list changed between when you searched and when processing finished, auto-advance will log a warning instead.

---

**Q: The times I enter — are they local time or UTC?**

All times entered in the filter fields are treated as **CET (Central European Time / Europe/Berlin)**. The application does not convert them to UTC. Ensure you enter the times as they appear in the CET production system logs.

---

**Q: Can I run a new Search while reprocessing is still in progress?**

Technically the UI allows it, but it is not recommended. Running a new search will clear the table and the `processed` tracker, which could cause confusion with in-flight reprocess results. Wait for the log to show `Reprocess All completed.` before running a new search.

---

**Q: The View Data window shows blank Order Numbers for some rows. Why?**

The Order Number is fetched via `FetchOrderBaseOnFG.sql`. If a record has no matching order in the database for the given filter parameters, the field will be blank. This does not affect reprocessing results.

