## 13. Glossary

| Term | Definition |
|---|---|
| **FG Serial Number** | Finished Goods serial number — the unique identifier of a manufactured product unit |
| **Pool** | A named processing pool in the job scheduling system (filtered to MI-type pools in ARM) |
| **Sync Queue / Synchronization Queue** | A named message queue through which FG data is synchronised to downstream systems |
| **CET** | Central European Time (Europe/Berlin timezone, UTC+1 in winter, UTC+2 in summer) |
| **Reprocess** | Re-submitting a previously failed message payload to the web service endpoint for another processing attempt |
| **Auto-Advance** | The automatic selection of the next Sync Queue after Reprocess All completes on the current queue |
| **ARM** | Automated Reprocess Manager — this application |
| **Web Service Endpoint** | The HTTP API (`WEB_SERVICES` in `.env`) that accepts message payloads for processing |
| **.env** | A plain-text configuration file containing environment variables (credentials, URLs) read at startup |
